|WKBSyntax: |YKBauction <item> <starting bid> [extra info]|WKB
|WKO=====================================================================
|YKOThe auction block is a live, world-wide auction called over the auction
channel. Only one item can be on the block at a time, mud-wide.

Selling: |YKBauction <item> <bid>|YKO hands an item from your inventory
to the auctioneer, who holds it in escrow while the bidding runs. The
starting bid must be at least 1000 coins. Worn, wielded, no-drop,
temporary, and soon-expiring unique items cannot be auctioned. If
nobody bids within 90 seconds the auction closes and the item comes
back to you; you can also |YKBstopauction|YKO before the first bid.
Either way, the auctioneer keeps a 100 coin handling fee.

Bidding: |YKBbid <amount>|YKO places a bid, and |YKBbid up|YKO offers
the next valid amount. Each bid must top the last by at least 250
coins. Bids are backed by your bank account, not your pockets: the
coins must be available in the bank, and a lien is held on them until
you are outbid or the auction ends. See |CKBhelp bank|YKO.

Winning and collecting: a minute after the last bid the auctioneer
calls going once, going twice, sold. The winner's coins are withdrawn
from the bank and the item is handed over on the spot (or set at your
feet if it is too heavy to carry). The seller's proceeds, minus the
auctioneer's 10% cut of the winning bid, are deposited straight into
the seller's bank account, even if the seller has since logged out.

|YKBauctioninfo|YKO shows the current item, seller, and high bid, and
|YKBauctionhist|YKO reviews recent auction traffic. You cannot start
or bid on an auction from rooms that block teleportation.|XX0

|WKBSee also: |YKBbank, market, economy|XX0

